dataset_description.json.Name: Neural activity induced by sensory stimulation can drive large-scale cerebrospinal fluid flow during wakefulness in humans
Funding: Simons Collaboration on Plasticity in the Aging Brain (no.811231)
National Defense Science and Engineering Graduate Fellowship

README:
This dataset contains 3T fMRI data from 16 subjects who completed a visual task involving a radial checkerboard that flickered at a rate of 4, 8, 12 or 40 Hz. Physiological data is available from each run, and contains pulse oximetry, respiration, and trigger channels.


The correct TR for all functional runs is 0.378 seconds.
